com.vmware.cis.tagging

Interface Category

  • All Superinterfaces:
    CategoryTypes, com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService, Service
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CategoryStub

    public interface Category
extends Service, CategoryTypes, com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService
    The Category interface provides methods to create, read, update, delete, and enumerate categories.

    • Method Detail

      • create

        Category.CreateInvocation create(CategoryTypes.CreateSpec createSpec)
        Creates a category. To invoke this method, you need the create category privilege.

        Invocation Result:
        The identifier of the created category. The return value will be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.cis.tagging.Category.

        Parameters:
        createSpec - Specification for the new category to be created.
        Returns:
        instance of Category.CreateInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described create operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        AlreadyExists - if the CategoryTypes.CreateSpec.getName() provided in the createSpec is the name of an already existing category.
        InvalidArgument - if any of the information in the createSpec is invalid.
        Unauthorized - if you do not have the privilege to create a category.

      • get

        Category.GetInvocation get(java.lang.String categoryId)
        Fetches the category information for the given category identifier. In order to view the category information, you need the read privilege on the category.

        Invocation Result:
        The CategoryModel that corresponds to categoryId.

        Parameters:
        categoryId - The identifier of the input category. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.cis.tagging.Category.
        Returns:
        instance of Category.GetInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described get operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        NotFound - if the category for the given categoryId does not exist in the system.
        Unauthorized - if you do not have the privilege to read the category.

                                 CategoryTypes.UpdateSpec updateSpec)
        Updates an existing category. To invoke this method, you need the edit privilege on the category.
        Parameters:

        updateSpec - Specification to update the category.

        InvalidArgument - if any of the information in the updateSpec is invalid.

        Unauthorized - if you do not have the privilege to update the category.

      • list

        Category.ListInvocation list()
        Enumerates the categories in the system. To invoke this method, you need the read privilege on the individual categories. The List will only contain those categories for which you have read privileges.

        Invocation Result:
        The List of resource identifiers for the categories in the system. The return value will contain identifiers for the resource type: com.vmware.cis.tagging.Category.

        Returns:
        instance of Category.ListInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described list operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.

      • listUsedCategories

        Category.ListUsedCategoriesInvocation listUsedCategories(java.lang.String usedByEntity)
        Enumerates all categories for which the usedByEntity is part of the CategoryModel.getUsedBy() subscribers Set. To invoke this method, you need the read privilege on the individual categories.

        Invocation Result:
        The List of resource identifiers for the categories in the system that are used by usedByEntity. The return value will contain identifiers for the resource type: com.vmware.cis.tagging.Category.

        Parameters:
        usedByEntity - The field on which the results will be filtered.
        Returns:
        instance of Category.ListUsedCategoriesInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described listUsedCategories operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.

      • addToUsedBy

        Category.AddToUsedByInvocation addToUsedBy(java.lang.String categoryId,
                                           java.lang.String usedByEntity)
        Adds the usedByEntity to the CategoryModel.getUsedBy() subscribers Set for the specified category. If the usedByEntity is already in the Set, then this becomes an idempotent no-op. To invoke this method, you need the modify CategoryModel.getUsedBy() privilege on the category.
        Parameters:
        categoryId - The identifier of the input category. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.cis.tagging.Category.
        usedByEntity - The name of the user to be added to the CategoryModel.getUsedBy() Set.
        Returns:
        instance of Category.AddToUsedByInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described addToUsedBy operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        NotFound - if the category for the given categoryId does not exist in the system.
        Unauthorized - if you do not have the privilege to add an entity to the CategoryModel.getUsedBy() field.

      • removeFromUsedBy

        Category.RemoveFromUsedByInvocation removeFromUsedBy(java.lang.String categoryId,
                                                     java.lang.String usedByEntity)
        Removes the usedByEntity from the CategoryModel.getUsedBy() subscribers Set. If the usedByEntity is not using this category, then this becomes a no-op. To invoke this method, you need the modify CategoryModel.getUsedBy() privilege on the category.
        Parameters:
        categoryId - The identifier of the input category. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.cis.tagging.Category.
        usedByEntity - The name of the user to be removed from the CategoryModel.getUsedBy() Set.
        Returns:
        instance of Category.RemoveFromUsedByInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described removeFromUsedBy operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        NotFound - if the category for the given categoryId does not exist in the system.
        Unauthorized - if you do not have the privilege to remove an entity from the CategoryModel.getUsedBy() field.

      • revokePropagatingPermissions

        Category.RevokePropagatingPermissionsInvocation revokePropagatingPermissions(java.lang.String categoryId)
        Revokes all propagating permissions on the given category. You should then attach a direct permission with tagging privileges on the given category. To invoke this method, you need category related privileges (direct or propagating) on the concerned category.
        Parameters:
        categoryId - The identifier of the input category. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.cis.tagging.Category.
        Returns:
        instance of Category.RevokePropagatingPermissionsInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described revokePropagatingPermissions operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        NotFound - if the category for the given categoryId does not exist in the system.
        Unauthorized - if you do not have the privilege to revoke propagating permissions on the category.
